<item>
            <title>[JDK-8305755] [JVMCI] missing barriers in CompilerToVM.readFieldValue for Reference.referent</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8305755</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>JVMCI provides the ability to reflectively read any field in a Java object.  During JIT compilation this is only used to read final fields but native image uses it for heap introspection.  In that case it&amp;#39;s possible to use it to read Reference.referent but the JVMCI code is using obj_field_acquire which doesn&amp;#39;t perform any of the GC barrier work.  Native image is always run with -XX:+UseParallelGC for performance but when running with G1 this code can read a weak reference that is going to be released.</description>
